## My recommendation

Since you're planning to learn **Spring Boot** after this project, I'd implement the features in this order:

### Customer Module (Complete first)

* ✅ Register
* ✅ Login
* ✅ Check Balance
* ✅ Deposit
* ✅ Withdraw
* ⏳ Transfer Money
* ⏳ Transaction History
* ⏳ Change Password

### Then Admin Module

* Admin Login
* View All Customers
* Search Customer
* Delete Customer
* View All Transactions

This gives you a complete Banking Management System that demonstrates:

* Core Java
* OOP
* JDBC
* MySQL
* SQL Joins
* Transactions
* Role-based access (Customer/Admin)

That's a solid project to showcase on your resume before moving on to Spring Boot.
